#: ../../openmvcam/tutorial/analog_io.rst:2
msgid "Analog IO"
msgstr "模拟IO"

#: ../../openmvcam/tutorial/analog_io.rst:4
msgid ""
"The OpenMV Cam has one analog I/O pin (P6) which can be used as an ADC "
"input or DAC output. Here's how to use it to read a voltage value between"
" 0V and 3.3V::"
msgstr "OpenMV Cam具有一个模拟I/"
"O引脚（P6），可用作ADC输入或DAC输出。以下是如何使用它来读取0V至3."
"3V之间的电压值::"

#: ../../openmvcam/tutorial/analog_io.rst:15
msgid ""
"The ADC has 12-bits of resolution so it will output a value between 0 and"
" 4095 for 0 to 3.3 volts. Finally, note that while the pin is in ADC mode"
" it is not 5V tolerant anymore."
msgstr "ADC具有12位的分辨率，因此它将输出0到4095之间的值，用于0至3."
"3伏特。最后，请注意，当引脚处于ADC模式时，它不再具有5V容忍性。"

#: ../../openmvcam/tutorial/analog_io.rst:19
msgid ""
"Next, to generate an analog output voltage you can put the I/O pin in DAC"
" mode::"
msgstr "接下来，要生成模拟输出电压，您可以将I/O引脚放入DAC模式::"

#: ../../openmvcam/tutorial/analog_io.rst:33
msgid ""
"The above code generates a sin wave on the I/O pin which will go from 0 "
"to 255 for 0 to 3.3 volts. Again, note that while the pin is in DAC mode "
"it is not 5V tolerant anymore."
msgstr ""
"以上代码在I/O引脚上生成一个正弦波，该正弦波将在0至255之间变化，对应于0至3."
"3伏特。同样，请注意，当引脚处于DAC模式时，它不再具有5V容忍性。"
